    println("  1. Schwarzschild orbits {2,3,6}M = divisors of P1 (PROVEN, Einstein GR)")
    println("  2. Exotic S7: |Theta7|=28=P2, dim=7=P1+1 (PROVEN, Kervaire-Milnor)")
    println("  3. phi(P2)=sigma(P1)=12: UNIQUE bridge (PROVEN, computational)")
    println("  4. Golay [24,12,8] = [sigma*phi, sigma, sigma-tau] (PROVEN)")
    println("  5. Galois solvability up to tau, unsolvable at sopfr (PROVEN)")
    println("  6. 6 Painleve transcendents = P1 (FACT)")
    println("  7. Lorentz group: 6=P1 generators (PROVEN)")
    println("  8. ALL fractal dims = log ratios of n=6 functions (PROVEN)")
    println("  9. tau(sigma(6))=6: period-2 fixed point (PROVEN)")
    println("  10. sigma-tau-phi=n UNIQUE to n=6 (PROVEN, to 50000)")
    println("")
    println("  ROOT THEOREM: n=6 uniqueness derives from TWO properties:")
    println("    A. 6 is perfect (sigma=2n)")
    println("    B. 6 is squarefree (rad=n)")
    println("  6 is the ONLY number satisfying BOTH.")
    println("")
    sep72()
    println("  n=6: The number where arithmetic functions close upon themselves.")
    sep72()
}

